Phillies Pitcher Cole Hamels Goes on Disabled List With Shoulder Injury

-- B y   M i c h a e l   B u t e a u
-- 
2011-08-23T19:51:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-23/phillies-pitcher-cole-hamels-goes-on-disabled-list-with-shoulder-injury.html
Philadelphia Phillies pitcher Cole Hamels will miss a start against the Florida Marlins on Aug. 26
due to inflammation in his pitching shoulder, the team said.  Hamels was placed on the disabled list by the Major League
Baseball team, retroactive to Aug. 13. The left-hander is
expected to start again against the  Cincinnati Reds  on Aug. 29,
the Philadelphia Inquirer  reported .  In 25 starts, Hamels has a 13-7 record with a 2.62 earned
run average and 155 strikeouts.  The Phillies lead the National League East with an 82-44
record following a 10-0 win over the  New York Mets  yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story: Michael Buteau in Atlanta
at   mbuteau@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  